WorldStage Newsonline– Julius Berger Plc, Hallmark Insurance Plc, NEM Insurance Plc, Prestige Assurance Plc, and Red Star Express Plc have joined others to fix dates for their board meetings to consider the financial statement for the third quarter (Q3) 2020 results. Julius Berger Nigeria Plc in a notice at the Nigerian Stock Exchnage (NSE) said its board audit committee will meet on Wednesday October 28, 2020 to consider the result of Q3 ending at September 30, 2020. The closed period will be between October 13 to 29, 2020. Consolidated Hallmark Insurance Plc said its board of directors’ meeting will hold on Wednesday, October 28, 2020 at 1:00 pm online for consideration and adoption of management report, board committees’ reports and unaudited financial statement for the period ended 30th September 2020. The Closed Period will be from today, 13th October, 2020 until twenty-four (24) hours after the 2020 Q3 Unaudited Financial Statements for the Period ended 30th September is released to the public. NEM Insurance Plc said the meeting of its Board of Directors is scheduled to hold on Thursday October 29, 2020 to consider amongst other things, the Unaudited Accounts and Financial Statements for the period ended September 30, 2020. A closed period commencing from October 14, 2020 until 24 hours after the Unaudited Accounts and Financial Statements have been filed with The Exchange. Prestige Assurance Plc said its 91st board meeting will hold on 30th October virtually for consideration of financial statement for the period ended 30th September 2020 and recapitalization of the company. The closed period of the company is to start from 14th October. Red Star Express Plc said its  board meeting will hold on October 29, 2020 at company’s office 4, Adola Ajayi Crescent, Mafoluku, Lagos to approve half year for the year ended 31st March 2021. The closed period for the company is to commence from October 14, 2020